@bittecnologia as kisiyuk said, you can't change the XML after it is signed. Not even one byte. Doing so changes the XML digest, and the signature as consequence.

I had a similar problem before, the requirements demanded that the XML didn't had explicit namespace prefixes, and I could only solve by monkey-patching the signxml code so the output XML used the default signature namespace without prefixes.

I think you need to do the same on this case... :confused:

