As to supporting both, I don't know where Numba is in terms of ARM support, but my intuition is that Cython/C support remains far more widespread across many platforms. (I just got a Raspberry Pi in the mail today, hence my sudden interest in ARM. =P) Additionally, debugging and profiling tools are also currently limited for Numba. If we get some performance regression like [this one](https://github.com/numba/numba/issues/2313), we have very little recourse (other than becoming LLVM experts).

Again, as I've said before, I'm bullish on Numba, but I think we should dip our toes in, rather than dive in head-first.

