The definition for a resource on the client-side should only be defined once - I wouldn't expect there to be repetition. That said, the same pattern could work with named urls:

```javascript
const Classroom = Resource.Model.extend({
  url_name: 'classroom_details',
  props: {
    name: String,
    members: Array,
  }
});

const ClassroomCollection = Resource.Collection.extend({
  url_name: 'classroom_list',
  model: classroom,
});
```

There is slight repetition in that the API is defined independently in both Python and Javascript, but that is a good thing so that the interfaces are explicit.

