As a quick fix - have you tried to use `Resource/Table.iter(cast=false)` to disable those checks?

In the [configure database settings](http://docs.deis.io/en/latest/managing_deis/running-deis-without-ceph/#configure-database-settings) step you specify a database `host`, `name`, `user` and `password`.

As long as you have this already existing, then the controller will take care of the rest.

If you have a database, and you would like to, for example, share it between your applications and Deis, then you can do something like this:

```
CREATE DATABASE deis;
CREATE USER deis WITH password 'deisisawesome';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE deis TO deis;
```

